      "message": "[info] Line 341: Mobility is captured only once at Impl construction. `JamiAccount::isMobile()` depends on runtime config (`proxyEnabled` and `deviceKey`), which a user can toggle after conversations are already loaded (e.g. enabling/disabling push notifications). In that case existing SwarmManagers keep the stale value and will advertise the wrong `is_mobile` flag. Consider propagating mobility changes to live conversations when the account config changes (call `swarmManager_-\u003esetMobility(...)` from the account\u0027s config-update path), or document that a restart is required. Not blocking, but worth tracking.",
